<FIRST>r i PM-Iran-Quake     10-27 0107</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Iran-Quake,0108</SECOND>
<HEAD>Tremor Shakes Tehran</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TEHRAN, Iran (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An earthquake measuring 4.5 on the Richter
scale shook Tehran and its environs during the night, the official
Islamic Republic News Agency reported today.
   The agency said the quake shook the city at 11:53 p.m. (4:23
p.m. GMT) Thursday. The epicenter, according to the Geophysics
Center at Tehran University, was registered at 31 miles northeast
of Tehran.
   Officials said there were no casualties or damage. A quake
measuring 4 on the Richter scale could inflict moderate damage. The
scale is based on the energy released by an earthquake as measured
by ground motion recorded by a seismograph.
</TEXT>
