<SECOND>AM-Craps Injury,0219</SECOND>
<HEAD>Appeals Court Says Man Who Hurt Crap-Shooting Hand In Casino Can
Sue</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TRENTON, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A state appeals court says a gambler can
sue Trump Castle Hotel and Casino because he hurt his hand while
tossing dice onto a craps table.
   In a ruling Thursday, the Appellate Division of Superior Court
reversed a lower court decision to dismiss plaintiff Vincent
Vecere's negligence lawsuit against Trump Castle.
   Vecere, a resident of Camden County in western New Jersey, said
he injured his hand when he struck a post on a craps table at Trump
Castle.
   ``I made a bet. I picked up the dice and it came out with a
number which I don't remember,'' Vecere testified in an earlier
court appearance. ``When they gave me two dice back, I picked the
dice up, and I wanted to hit that back wall, and I swung to hit the
wall backward and I hit something. It was right here by the table
... I noticed there was a post there and I hurt my hand on the
post.''
   Vecere testified that he didn't see the post before he struck
his hand.
   Saying he thought he could shrug it off, Vecere continued to
play until his hand began to swell about three hours later.
