<SECOND>AM-News Carrier Rescue,0199</SECOND>
<HEAD>News Carrier Commended for Saving Life</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RAMSEY, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 14-year-old newspaper carrier is credited
with saving the life of an elderly woman who had spent 10 days
lying on her back in a bathtub.
   Christy Wenrich alerted police last week after she noticed a
pile of newspapers on the stoop of 83-year-old Ellen Gilmour's
home. Miss Wenrich had just resumed delivering The Record of
Hackensack after her sister had taken over the route for a few days.
   When police went to Mrs. Gilmour's home, they heard faint pleas
for help coming from inside. ``They broke into the back and found
her in the bathtub on her back,'' said Ramsey Police Captain
Anthony Del Colliano.
   Mrs. Gilmour told police she had been cleaning the tub when she
fell in 10 days before her rescue.
   Mrs. Gilmour was in fair condition Friday at The Valley Hospital
in Ridgewood, spokeswoman Marylou Zeug said.
   Ramsey acting police chief Richard A. Franceschi said he doesn't
believe Mrs. Gilmour would have survived if Miss Wenrich hadn't
tipped off authorities.
   The Ramsey Borough Council plans to publicly commend Miss
Wenrich at its meeting Nov. 14.
