<TEXT>
   Author Alex Haley urged high school
students to be selfish when planning their futures.
   Haley spent part of Thursday talking to students at two high
schools.
   ``What I recommend is that you be a little selfish. Think not of
the group, but give some thought for a while about yourself,'' he
told about 1,000 students at Vicksburg High School.
   ``The truth is, what you do now is going to dictate what you're
doing at 30 or 40,'' he said.
   Haley won a Pultizer Price in 1977 for his book, ``Roots: The
Story of an American Family.''
