<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The son of Australian turkey farmers landed the
starring role in the most eagerly awaited stage show in London _
Stephen Sondheim's ``Sunday in the Park with George.''
   Actor Philip Quast, 32, will play French painter Georges Seurat
in the British version of the musical by Sondheim and James Lapine.
In New York, the show ran for 540 performances and won the 1985
Pulitzer Prize for drama.
   The musical opens in London on March 15.
   Maria Friedman will co-star as Dot, a part originated by
Bernadette Peters on Broadway.
   Quast, who comes from the Australian town of Tamworth, 250 miles
northwest of Sydney, said he would have been a fisherman if his
acting career hadn't panned out.
   ``They're both quite solitary things,'' he said.
