<HEAD>Texas-Based Air Force Planes Seeking Marijuana Fields</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: ADDS one graf comment from Texas base, CORRECTS spelling Hickam
in 4th graf: ``The four,''</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four Air Force reconnaissance planes are
searching the Hawaiian Islands for marijuana fields as the crews
are flying training missions there, the Pentagon said Friday.
   The RF-4C reconnaissance planes are from the 67th Tactical
Reconnaissance Wing at Bergstrom Air Force Base in Texas, said
Defense Department spokesman Army Maj. John Smith.
