contracts through collective bargaining from January through
September won average annual wage increases of 3.1 percent compared
to average gains of 2.4 percent in their prior contracts, the Labor
Department said.
   The data in Thursday's report covers contracts for 1.3 million
workers negotiated in the first nine months of the year.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Summertime sales incentives eroded the Big Three
automakers' third-quarter profits, which skidded a combined 27.3
percent from record levels a year ago.
   General Motors Corp., Ford Motor Co. and Chrysler Corp. reported
Thursday combined earnings for the three-month period of $1.33
billion on revenues of $56.92 billion. That compared with an
industry third-quarter record profit last year of $1.83 billion on
revenues of $56.48 billion.
