from New York City to a Dallas suburb, where the world's largest
oil company will join other corporate giants that have fled the
Northeast to exploit Texas's depressed real estate market.
   Exxon said Thursday it plans to move its 300 headquarters jobs
to Las Colinas, a development in the Dallas suburb of Irving.
Factors Exxon cited included employee living costs, costs of doing
business and the overall business climate.
