   The stock market headed lower again today,
extending its week-long decline amid worries over weakness in
corporate earnings.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials dropped 8.20 to 2,605.53
by 11 a.m. on Wall Street.
   Losers outnumbered gainers by nearly 2 to 1 in nationwide
trading of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 410 up, 766
