<HEAD>Fixed-Rate Home Mortgages Average 9.82 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fixed-rate home mortgages averaged 9.82
percent this week, the lowest level since early August, the Federal
Home Loan Mortgage Corp. said Friday.
   That rate was down from 9.92 percent last week and was the
lowest since fixed-rate mortgages averaged 9.68 percent the week
ending Aug. 4.
   On 1-year adjustable-rate mortgages, lenders were asking an
average initial rate of 8.58 percent this week, the same as the
week before, Freddie Mac said.
